FBI agents obtained legal permission to retrieve data from San Bernardino Shooter, Syed Rizwan Farook\'s I-Phone. But thanks to an Apple security feature, the agency hasn\'t been able to access the phone without wiping the data. That\'s because the I -Phone\'s have a security feature that wipes all the data after 10 failed passcode attempts and the FBI could risk loosing all possible critical information. 

In a public letter, Cook wrote that the court order to help the agency is a dangerous breach of privacy. \"They are not asking apple to redesign its product or to create a new backdoor to one of their products. They\'re simply asking for something that would have an impact on this one device,\" said White House Press Secretary, Josh Earnest in a press conference earlier this week.

